node.text:
⁣
This is a powerful story about judgment. It’s so easy to judge people when we are clouded with our own emotions.⁣
⁣
Mindfulness means stepping out of the washing machine of emotions and observing them. Empathy means looking through the eye of the other. Combine them both and you have the “wise-mind” state. Simply remember this, everyone you meet is fighting a battle you know nothing about.

node.title: LEAVE A ❤️ IF THIS TOUCHED YOU.⁣

node.text:
I’m so proud of @simonebiles and @naomiosaka for leading the way and putting their mental health first.⁣
⁣
Vulnerability is true strength and I applaud them exhibiting vulnerability especially being in such a powerful position in sports. ⁣
⁣
❤️

node.title: DROP A ❤️ IF YOU FEEL THAT MENTAL HEALTH IS IMPORTANT

Single does NOT mean lonely and relationship does NOT mean happy. Sometimes people look at being single as a bad thing, it's not.

Being single can allow you to reflect and grow individually and once you do that, you can attract people who are like-minded.

node.text:
DID YOU EAT LUNCHABLES WHEN YOU WERE A KID? LISTEN UP 👇 

Geoffrey Bible, former CEO of Philip Morris (Lunchables), was quoted as saying, “If you take Lunchables apart, the most healthy item in it is the napkin.”

In an apparent effort to squash this image, Kraft discontinued its Maxed Out Lunchables in 2009, including a cheese and ham option with 660 calories and 22 grams of fat. Those numbers earned the meal first place on a list of the “Five Worst Packaged Lunchbox Meals” by the Cancer Project at the time.

If you are purposefully staying away from cigarettes you should consider staying away from processed meats as well - they could be having the same longterm affect on your body.

node.text:
DROP A 🔥 IF YOU’RE GOING TO BAN BURNED FOOD FROM YOUR DIET

Just overheating, let alone burning some foods can lead to the formation of compounds linked to cancer. Put a STOP to this in your diet today.

According to the National Center for Biotechnology Information, burnt toast contains acrylamide. If you’ve never heard of it, it’s a compound commonly used to produce a variety of products, including cosmetics, toiletries, dyes, fabrics, papers, and textiles. However, it can also form in starchy foods during high-heat cooking methods according to the FDA.

Dietary acrylamide has been linked to several negative health effects, but most notably - cancer. In fact, in 1994 the International Agency for Research on Cancer classified acrylamide as a probable carcinogen in humans.
